				\begin{document}$$h_{{\mathrm{SNP}}}^2$$\end{document}hSNP2) for the covariate risk factors, and sampling covariance between SNP effects estimated from potentially overlapping samples, all of which can be computed from summary data (Methods; Supplementary Tables 7–10). Given the similar GSMR results between BMI and WHRadjBMI and between SBP and DBP (Supplementary Fig. 10), we did not include DBP and WHRadjBMI in the conditional analysis to avoid over-correction.

